  "texts": [
    "Information extraction refers to the structured processing of information contained in text into a specific structure of organization [12].",
    "The typical information extraction tasks include NER and event extraction [13].www.ijacsa.thesai.org  NER refers to the extraction of entities in text; the entities are usually small pieces of phrases describing certain concepts.",
    "The example of NER in fund prospectus is the valuation day.",
    "The phrase 'Weekly, each Tuesday' explains the day for valuation.",
    "However, there are many dates in fund prospectuses; only this date indicates the valuation day, making this entity hard to identify."
  ],
